6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Both platforms calculate funding rates hourly using similar mark price to index price differentials. Hyperliquid's on-chain order book provides more transparent price discovery, while Drift's vAMM system can create temporary rate divergences during high volatility. Hyperliquid's independent L1 eliminates network congestion affecting rate calculations, whereas Drift benefits from Solana's speed but remains subject to network conditions. Both use 8-hour TWAPs for rate smoothing but Hyperliquid's implementation is fully verifiable on-chain."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which platform offers better funding rate arbitrage opportunities?","answer":"Hyperliquid's transparent on-chain order book and independent network provide more predictable rate calculations. Drift's JIT liquidity can offer better execution but with added complexity in rate mechanics."},{"question":"How do the 1-hour funding intervals compare between platforms?","answer":"Both use identical 1-hour intervals, but Hyperliquid's calculations are fully on-chain and verifiable. Drift's rates can be influenced by Solana network conditions during high congestion periods."},{"question":"What are the key risks for arbitrageurs on each platform?","answer":"Hyperliquid risks include USDC-only settlements and newer platform maturity. Drift faces Solana dependency risks and potential vAMM slippage during volatile periods affecting arbitrage profitability."},{"question":"Which platform has lower overall trading costs for arbitrage?","answer":"Both charge identical maker/taker fees of 0.02%/0.05%. However, Hyperliquid eliminates gas fees through its L1 design, while Drift benefits from Solana's low transaction costs of ~$0.00025 per transaction."}]}]
